  <li>format is <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">title followed by blank line followed by rest of the post in markdown format</code> for example:
<strong>Start of awesome post in a checkvist list item</strong>
    <div class="language-markdown highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>awesome title
awesome rest of the post. <span class="gs">**awesome bold text**</span>
</code></pre></div>    </div>
    <p><strong>End of awesome post in a checkvist list item</strong></p>
  </li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/rtanglao/rt-checkvist/blob/main/without-link-blogthis.rb">without-link-blogthis.rb</a> autocreates the slug from the first line of a list item in a checkvist list (using the title with stop words removed)</li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/rtanglao/rt-checkvist/blob/main/linkless_blog_all_open.rb">linkless_blog_all_open.rb</a> calls without_blogthis.rb to create blog posts in jekyll format from my all open list items in my â€˜blog thisâ€™ <a href="https://checkvist.com/checklists/936619">checkvist list 936619</a> after you type â€˜yâ€™ to approve it</li>
